\] Now we sum these remainders: \[
1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 5 = 15
\] Finally, we find the remainder when 15 is divided by 8: \[
15 \div 8 = 1 \text{ remainder } 7 \quad \Rightarrow \quad 15 \equiv 7 \pmod{8}
\] Therefore, the remainder when \(7145 + 7146 + 7147 + 7148 + 7149\) is divided by 8 is \(\boxed{7}\). </answer>

